@page "/"

<PageTitle>SpawnDev.RTC - WebRTC Everywhere</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1>SpawnDev.RTC</h1>
    <p class="lead">Cross-platform WebRTC for .NET - browser and desktop from a single API.</p>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-md-8">
            <h4>What is SpawnDev.RTC?</h4>
            <p>
                SpawnDev.RTC provides a unified WebRTC interface that works identically in
                Blazor WebAssembly (using native browser WebRTC) and on desktop .NET
                (using a bundled <a href="https://github.com/sipsorcery-org/sipsorcery" target="_blank">SipSorcery</a> fork
                with proven browser-interop DTLS/SRTP).
            </p>
            <p>
                Write your peer connection, data channel, and signaling code once - it runs everywhere.
            </p>

            <h4 class="mt-4">Features</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>True cross-platform</strong> - Browser (Blazor WASM) and desktop (.NET 10)</li>
                <li><strong>Browser-proven DTLS/SRTP</strong> - Desktop peers connect to Chrome, Firefox, Edge</li>
                <li><strong>Data channels</strong> - Reliable and unreliable with full DCEP support</li>
                <li><strong>ICE with STUN/TURN</strong> - Full candidate gathering and relay fallback</li>
                <li><strong>No native dependencies</strong> - Pure C# on desktop, native browser APIs in WASM</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 class="mt-4">Built With</h4>
            <p>
                The desktop WebRTC stack is powered by
                <a href="https://github.com/sipsorcery-org/sipsorcery" target="_blank">SipSorcery</a>
                by <strong>Aaron Clauson</strong> and contributors - the only pure C# WebRTC implementation
                for .NET. SipSorcery provides the complete ICE, DTLS, SCTP, and data channel stack
                without any native wrappers or C++ dependencies.
            </p>
            <p>
                Browser interop is powered by
                <a href="https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.BlazorJS" target="_blank">SpawnDev.BlazorJS</a>
                with typed C# wrappers for all browser WebRTC APIs.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Links</h5>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled">
                        <li><a href="https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.RTC" target="_blank">GitHub</a></li>
                        <li><a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/SpawnDev.RTC" target="_blank">NuGet</a></li>
                        <li><a href="https://github.com/sipsorcery-org/sipsorcery" target="_blank">SipSorcery (upstream)</a></li>
                        <li><a href="https://github.com/LostBeard/SpawnDev.BlazorJS" target="_blank">SpawnDev.BlazorJS</a></li>
                    </ul>
                    <h5 class="card-title mt-3">Test</h5>
                    <p><a href="/tests" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Run Unit Tests</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
